  Given list of integers, return list in strange ordre.
  Strange sorting, is when you start iwth the minimum value,
  then maximmu of the remaining integers, then imnimum and so on.

  Examples:
  strangeSortList([1, 2, 3, 4]) == [1, 4, 2, 3]
